alesforce, Next Step, or the call. Venkat is preparing an internal business case with budget approval pending (AIS_Why), so co-building a numbers-backed ROI he can defend is the highest-leverage metrics move before proposal finalization."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["OpportunityContactRole: Venkata Masetty", "Avoma demo 2026-06-17 (agenda ownership, questioning)", "Next Step (follow-up items shared by Venkat 06-03/06-19)"], "narrative": "Venkata Masetty (Group Category Manager - Coatings) is the confirmed champion and internal project lead for the Supplier Integrated Platform. He set and owned the demo agenda, drove the most detailed use-case questioning, is the primary Zycus contact across the RFP cycle, and is authoring the internal business case for budget approval. His advocacy is active in driving the evaluation, but there are still gaps: he has not shared competitive intel, has not introduced Zycus to the budget signatory, and his engagement remains largely responsive to Zycus asks rather than proactively selling internally. He has access to procurement leadership (Sharon Moar, Jeremy Dussel) who attend his sessions. Converting him from evaluation-driver to internal seller, armed with a quantified ROI, is the key champion move."}, "competition": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Competitors__c (blank)", "Avoma demo 2026-06-17 (no rival named)", "Prior canonical record (competitive landscape unknown, carried forward)"], "narrative": "No competitor is named in any source: Competitors__c is blank, and no rival is mentioned in Next Step, tasks, or the 17 Jun demo transcript (Caroline's prior tenure 'at Coupa' is her own background, not a BMI alternative, and must not be read as a competitor). For a formal, RFP-led $180k enterprise S2C deal a multi-vendor shortlist is highly likely, so the absence of intel is a blind spot rather than evidence of a sole source. Per living memory this stays an open unknown carried forward, not a fabricated name.